nated book  On Killing  The Psychological Cost of Learning to Kill in War and Society  In the book  he argues that today s media has picked up on the techniques used by armies to teach soldiers to kill  in spite of humans  inborn aversion to killing  and that the media is thus responsible for the rising rate of school shootings and other violent acts among the young  On Killing is on the U S  Marine Corps Commandant s required reading list and is also required reading at the Federal Bureau of Investigations academy  One of the world s foremost experts on killing and human violence in general  Grossman helped to train mental health professionals after the Jonesboro  Ark  school shooting  and has also been involved with either counseling or court cases in the wake of the Paducah  Springfield  Littleton  Virginia Tech  and Nickel Mines Amish school shootings  In addition  Grossman served as a member of the prosecutor s team in the case against convicted Oklahoma City bomber Timothy McVeigh  Today  he spends over three quarters of the year on the road training law enforcement and military personnel  Grossman is a member of the American Board for Certification in Homeland Security and the American College of Forensic Examiners Institute  Grossman s talk is part of the H B  Johnson Jr   26 Distinguished Lecture Series   VMI  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 